87
00:06:58,932 --> 00:07:00,427
or do something else, or?

88
00:07:00,427 --> 00:07:02,656
- I know, but working
with Ashton in bookkeeping

89
00:07:02,656 --> 00:07:05,435
is where I want you to start.

90
00:07:05,435 --> 00:07:08,518
Robert will supervise, is that clear?

91
00:07:09,935 --> 00:07:12,546
- Excuse me, Dad, may I be excused?

92
00:07:12,546 --> 00:07:16,402
I would like to go talk
to, to Ash, please.

93
00:07:16,402 --> 00:07:17,439
- All right.

94
00:07:17,439 --> 00:07:19,356
- Thank you, thank you.

95
00:07:22,985 --> 00:07:25,069
- Simon, you have something to say?

96
00:07:25,069 --> 00:07:27,236
- Yeah, I say it's unfair.

97
00:07:29,009 --> 00:07:30,279
This is a joke, right?

98
00:07:30,279 --> 00:07:32,630
- Well, everything's a joke to you.

99
00:07:32,630 --> 00:07:34,239
- What I mean

100
00:07:34,239 --> 00:07:37,230
is that Joe is just handed everything,

101
00:07:37,230 --> 00:07:38,808
opportunities none of the rest of us had,

102
00:07:38,808 --> 00:07:40,934
like this so-called apprenticeship?

103
00:07:40,934 --> 00:07:42,900
- What have you done with
your opportunities, Simon?

104
00:07:42,900 --> 00:07:44,060
- Oh, Jacob, not now.

105
00:07:44,060 --> 00:07:45,151
- Thrown them away.

106
00:07:45,151 --> 00:07:46,680
Got yourself a police record.

107
00:07:46,680 --> 00:07:49,212
In the process, dragged
Lee here into the mess

108
00:07:49,212 --> 00:07:50,628
just for good measure.

109
00:07:50,628 --> 00:07:52,665
Is that what you mean by unfair?

110
00:07:52,665 --> 00:07:53,699
- I was a kid.

111
00:07:53,699 --> 00:07:54,935
- When are you gonna grow up?

112
00:07:54,935 --> 00:07:55,768
- Jacob.

113
00:07:58,163 --> 00:08:00,080
- All right, all right.

114
00:08:02,081 --> 00:08:03,998
I'm sorry, I apologize.

115
00:08:06,197 --> 00:08:10,364
The past can't be undone,
but it can be learned from.

116
00:08:12,327 --> 00:08:15,910
I'd like to show you
something, all of you.

117
00:08:18,121 --> 00:08:19,372
Take at a look at this,

118
00:08:19,372 --> 00:08:23,205
if you wanna know what
unfair can really mean.

119
00:08:33,944 --> 00:08:36,527
(horn blowing)

120
00:08:38,694 --> 00:08:41,694
(upbeat rock music)

121
00:08:43,123 --> 00:08:44,552
- Good morning.

122
00:08:44,552 --> 00:08:45,520
Say, you're early.

123
00:08:45,520 --> 00:08:48,633
- Yeah, I was trying to impress the boss.

124
00:08:48,633 --> 00:08:51,054
And this coffee, ugh.

125
00:08:51,054 --> 00:08:54,221
I thought we ran a successful company.

126
00:08:55,859 --> 00:08:57,859
- Ooh, oh, you're fired.

127
00:08:59,245 --> 00:09:01,155
Just kidding.

128
00:09:01,155 --> 00:09:03,239
Uh, you've been here.

129
00:09:03,239 --> 00:09:05,445
My office there, keep your
grubby fingers off my desk.

130
00:09:05,445 --> 00:09:09,278
Come on, I'll give you
the new employees tour.

131
00:09:13,698 --> 00:09:17,507
You'll find Grant in these
departments, most of the time.

132
00:09:17,507 --> 00:09:19,674
(singing)

133
00:09:23,051 --> 00:09:25,791
Oh here it is, your desk.

134
00:09:25,791 --> 00:09:27,208
Get to work, now.

135
00:09:30,650 --> 00:09:31,817
Got you again.

136
00:09:33,245 --> 00:09:37,245
We just moved Simon into
that office over there.

137
00:09:38,365 --> 00:09:40,739
It's closer to his department.

138
00:09:40,739 --> 00:09:43,630
Sometimes, you're gonna find Lee there.

139
00:09:43,630 --> 00:09:45,213
But well, you know.

140
00:09:47,217 --> 00:09:49,684
Hey, guys, come on, what is this?

141
00:09:49,684 --> 00:09:50,517
Look, huh?

142
00:09:54,439 --> 00:09:55,272
- Hi, Ash.

143
00:10:10,324 --> 00:10:13,157
(dramatic noises)

144
00:10:15,792 --> 00:10:18,125
(explosion)

145
00:10:34,881 --> 00:10:38,254
- Hey, hey hey hey, are you all right?

146
00:10:38,254 --> 00:10:41,540
- Come on, let's get him inside.

147
00:10:41,540 --> 00:10:42,539
- Maybe you should go home.

148
00:10:42,539 --> 00:10:44,806
- No, I'm fine, really I'm fine, you guys.

149
00:10:44,806 --> 00:10:48,820
- Ash, Ash please, would
you mind repeating that?

150
00:10:48,820 --> 00:10:52,475
- Our dear little egg white half-brother

