00:16:27,736 --> 00:16:29,458
I made it, with these old hands,

267
00:16:29,458 --> 00:16:33,227
so I'm not so sure I
haven't lost my touch.

268
00:16:33,227 --> 00:16:34,810
- I don't think so.

269
00:16:35,648 --> 00:16:37,308
Not hardly, I would say.

270
00:16:37,308 --> 00:16:39,954
- [Jacob] Not bad, not bad.

271
00:16:39,954 --> 00:16:41,529
I mean, I haven't touched
a needle and thread

272
00:16:41,529 --> 00:16:43,726
for 15 years, but not
bad if I say so myself.

273
00:16:43,726 --> 00:16:45,929
- Not bad at all.

274
00:16:45,929 --> 00:16:47,596
Thank you very much.

275
00:16:49,481 --> 00:16:51,263
But why this?

276
00:16:51,263 --> 00:16:54,253
What did I do to deserve this, why now?

277
00:16:54,253 --> 00:16:56,503
- I'm proud of you, Joseph.

278
00:16:57,359 --> 00:16:59,350
My hopes are with you.

279
00:16:59,350 --> 00:17:01,793
Well, let's just say that
this marks the beginning

280
00:17:01,793 --> 00:17:04,043
of what I expect will be a,

281
00:17:04,905 --> 00:17:07,738
a very successful career and life.

282
00:17:09,009 --> 00:17:10,983
- How you holding up?

283
00:17:10,983 --> 00:17:14,783
- Okay, for now, ask me again in an hour.

284
00:17:14,783 --> 00:17:16,004
- Is everyone here?

285
00:17:16,004 --> 00:17:17,148
- Yeah, I think so.

286
00:17:17,148 --> 00:17:18,898
- I haven't seen Joe.

287
00:17:21,008 --> 00:17:22,175
- I hate this.

288
00:17:23,057 --> 00:17:24,305
How could he do this?

289
00:17:24,305 --> 00:17:28,288
How could he just stab
us in the back like that?

290
00:17:28,288 --> 00:17:29,762
- Well why not?

291
00:17:29,762 --> 00:17:31,504
This is Daddy's good little boy.

292
00:17:31,504 --> 00:17:34,226
A shining example to us all.

293
00:17:34,226 --> 00:17:36,183
Joe isn't one of us.

294
00:17:36,183 --> 00:17:39,538
But as long as he's around
doing Daddy's little spying,

295
00:17:39,538 --> 00:17:41,697
we're all gonna be under the microscope.

296
00:17:41,697 --> 00:17:43,407
- So what are we gonna do about it?

297
00:17:43,407 --> 00:17:44,240
- Nothing.

298
00:17:45,093 --> 00:17:46,310
Not yet.

299
00:17:46,310 --> 00:17:49,604
- Joseph was right in coming to me.

300
00:17:49,604 --> 00:17:52,541
And I think, Robert, if you're honest

301
00:17:52,541 --> 00:17:54,647
with yourself, you'll agree.

302
00:17:54,647 --> 00:17:55,480
- Yes.

303
00:17:56,389 --> 00:17:58,158
- And you realize that
there are consequences

304
00:17:58,158 --> 00:17:59,720
for your actions?

305
00:17:59,720 --> 00:18:00,637
- Yes, sir.

306
00:18:01,498 --> 00:18:04,128
- I will not be signing
the business over to you

307
00:18:04,128 --> 00:18:05,878
next fall as planned.

308
00:18:07,077 --> 00:18:11,244
I will be releasing it to you,
conditionally, in five years.

309
00:18:14,547 --> 00:18:16,458
- Five years, oh, Father.

310
00:18:16,458 --> 00:18:19,934
- I need to know that you can
run the business, profitably,

311
00:18:19,934 --> 00:18:24,101
without resorting to intolerable
solutions to problems.

312
00:18:27,168 --> 00:18:30,239
If you want to work with us,
you'll be going to New York

313
00:18:30,239 --> 00:18:33,406
next week as planned to secure a loan.

314
00:18:34,703 --> 00:18:38,703
And taking Ashton and
Simon and Joseph with you.

315
00:18:41,173 --> 00:18:44,145
- Robert, I know you're angry with me,

316
00:18:44,145 --> 00:18:46,395
but just hear me out, okay?

317
00:18:47,901 --> 00:18:50,713
I've been studying the
market with my eye towards

318
00:18:50,713 --> 00:18:54,573
getting us very very
favorable terms on a loan.

319
00:18:54,573 --> 00:18:55,878
I'll give you my advice.

320
00:18:55,878 --> 00:18:58,834
You don't have to take it, but I'm betting

321
00:18:58,834 --> 00:19:02,667
I can get you the best
terms you've ever seen.

322
00:19:03,629 --> 00:19:04,629
- All right.

323
00:19:07,959 --> 00:19:12,042
But, the final decision
on the loan, that's mine.

324
00:19:14,031 --> 00:19:14,948
- Yes, yes.

325
00:19:22,536 --> 00:19:23,369
All right.

326
00:19:28,016 --> 00:19:29,581
- Justin.

327
00:19:29,581 --> 00:19:30,997
- Simon, I thought you'd left.

328
00:19:30,997 --> 00:19:32,294
- No, I just wanted to talk to Ash

329
00:19:32,294 --> 00:19:34,035
about what happened downstairs.

330
00:19:34,035 --> 00:19:35,689
Robert got the worst of it.

331
00:19:35,689 --> 00:19:37,838
- Ash didn't fare much better.

332
00:19:37,838 --> 00:19:39,277
I was gonna go talk to him.

333
00:19:39,277 --> 00:19:41,291
- He'll be okay.

334
00:19:41,291 --> 00:19:43,979
- We all got a chewing out.

335
00:19:43,979 --> 00:19:46,735
Our little half-brother
should feel very proud.

336
00:19:46,735 --> 00:19:48,902
There's nothing we can do.

337
00:19:50,684 --> 00:19:53,601
- Yeah, I'm not so sure about that.

338
00:19:58,048 --> 00:20:00,916
(upbeat music)

339
00:20:00,916 --> 00:20:03,833
- Oh, Tattinger, way to go, Robert.

340
00:20:07,370 --> 00:20:10,286
- Here's to a job well done.

341
00:20:10,286 --> 00:20:14,369
Loan terms that brought
tears to a banker's eyes.

342
00:20:16,408 --> 00:20:19,369
- [Ashton] So what's
the plan for tomorrow?

343
00:20:19,369 --> 00:20:21,372
- How about some sightseeing?

344
00:20:21,372 --> 00:20:22,429
Huh?

345
00:20:22,429 --> 00:20:24,455
We got two days to kill.

346
00:20:24,455 --> 00:20:25,538
- Yeah, sure.

347
00:20:27,287 --> 00:20:29,539
- Man, what a day.

348
00:20:29,539 --> 00:20:31,039
I've about had it.

349
00:20:33,532 --> 00:20:35,389
- I'll tuck you in, come on.

350
00:20:35,389 --> 00:20:38,461
- Yeah, yeah, good night, Robert.

351
00:20:38,461 --> 00:20:40,517
- Good night, you guys.

352
00:20:40,517 --> 00:20:43,100
(upbeat music)

353
00:20:45,086 --> 00:20:46,705
Okay.

354
00:20:46,705 --> 00:20:50,872
All right, well, I guess
I'll see you tomorrow, right?

355
00:20:51,970 --> 00:20:53,985
- Yeah, good night, Joe.

356
00:20:53,985 --> 00:20:56,568
(upbeat music)

357
00:21:01,521 --> 00:21:02,854
- I tried, Lord.

358
00:21:07,651 --> 00:21:08,734
I really did.

359
00:21:10,664 --> 00:21:11,497
But,

360
00:21:12,544 --> 00:21:15,127
they're still so angry with me.

361
00:21:18,031 --> 00:21:20,448
I don't know what else to do.

362
00:21:37,555 --> 00:21:39,670
- Can I come in?

363
00:21:39,670 --> 00:21:40,753
- Yeah, yeah.

364
00:21:44,326 --> 00:21:45,789
What time is it?

365
00:21:45,789 --> 00:21:47,289
- It's about 8:30.

366
00:21:48,718 --> 00:21:49,551
- Oh yeah?

367
00:21:50,955 --> 00:21:52,205
- Look, Joseph,

368
00:21:54,229 --> 00:21:57,422
I know things have been bad recently.

369
00:21:57,422 --> 00:22:00,589
I think, well, can I say we all think,

370
00:22:01,843 --> 00:22:05,510
maybe it's about time
we buried the hatchet.

371
00:22:07,343 --> 00:22:10,657
What about it, how do you feel?

372
00:22:10,657 --> 00:22:12,907
- I don't know what to say.

373
00:22:15,148 --> 00:22:16,956
- Well, why don't you get yourself ready

374
00:22:16,956 --> 00:22:18,419
and join Ash and me?

375
00:22:18,419 --> 00:22:20,636
We're going out on a little
excursion this morning

376
00:22:20,636 --> 00:22:22,225
while we're waiting for Robert.

377
00:22:22,225 --> 00:22:23,462
- Oh yeah?

378
00:22:23,462 --> 00:22:24,295
Where to?

379
00:22:25,402 --> 00:22:27,819
- It's a manufacturing plant.

380
00:22:28,798 --> 00:22:31,096
Actually, it oughta be pretty interesting.

381
00:22:31,096 --> 00:22:33,707
Seeing how one of these
local operations is run.

382
00:22:33,707 --> 00:22:35,290
- Yeah, yeah, yeah.

383
00:22:38,153 --> 00:22:38,986
Ooh.

384
00:22:40,336 --> 00:22:42,983
Give me about 15 minutes.

385
00:22:42,983 --> 00:22:44,634
- Good.

386
00:22:44,634 --> 00:22:46,886
See you in the lobby, champ.

387
00:22:46,886 --> 00:22:49,803
(mysterious music)

388
00:23:12,006 --> 00:23:12,839
- Kellers.

389
00:23:14,213 --> 00:23:15,516
We're expected.

390
00:23:15,516 --> 00:23:18,433
(mysterious music)

391
00:23:47,139 --> 00:23:49,615
- Not the best part of town, is it?

392
00:23:49,615 --> 00:23:52,138
- Serves the purpose.

393
00:23:52,138 --> 00:23:52,971
Joseph.

394
00:24:10,618 --> 00:24:12,001
- Good morning, gentlemen.

395
00:24:12,001 --> 00:24:12,834
Frisk him.

396
00:24:18,572 --> 00:24:20,823
- They don't take any chances, do they?

397
00:24:20,823 --> 00:24:22,448
- Can't afford to.

398
00:24:22,448 --> 00:24:23,615
- Right there.

399
00:24:29,369 --> 00:24:30,702
- Trade secrets.

400
00:25:06,873 --> 00:25:10,344
- [Thompsonn] Mister
Childress, they are all here.

401
00:25:10,344 --> 00:25:13,094
- Good, let's get this over with.

402
00:25:13,932 --> 00:25:15,349
- This is Ashton.

403
00:25:16,724 --> 00:25:17,891
That's Joseph.

404
00:25:19,850 --> 00:25:20,850
- Gentlemen.

405
00:25:23,080 --> 00:25:25,437
(grunting)

406
00:25:25,437 --> 00:25:29,604
- Just get the coat off him,
and then we're finished here.

407
00:25:31,350 --> 00:25:32,634
- I think I was clear on what will happen

408
00:25:32,634 --> 00:25:34,389
if this is not the agreed upon amount.

409
00:25:34,389 --> 00:25:36,139
- What are you doing?

410
00:25:37,181 --> 00:25:38,806
- No.

411
00:25:38,806 --> 00:25:39,639
No, buddy.

412
00:25:41,074 --> 00:25:42,595
- It's too late for all that.

413
00:25:42,595 --> 00:25:43,529
Now listen to me.

414
00:25:43,529 --> 00:25:45,159
Listen to me, listen.

415
00:25:45,159 --> 00:25:45,992
Are you listening?

416
00:25:45,992 --> 00:25:46,825
- Yeah.

417
00:25:47,940 --> 00:25:51,436
- From this point on,
he's as good as dead.

418
00:25:51,436 --> 00:25:53,853
Do you understand, that's it.

419
00:25:55,755 --> 00:25:57,107
Let me deal with this, okay?

420
00:25:57,107 --> 00:25:57,940
- Okay.

421
00:26:02,190 --> 00:26:03,788
- I need the coat.

422
00:26:03,788 --> 00:26:04,621
- Take it.

423
00:26:11,819 --> 00:26:13,642
- All right, he's all yours.

424
00:26:13,642 --> 00:26:16,839
As far as we're concerned,
he never existed.

425
00:26:16,839 --> 00:26:18,772
That's what we paid you for.

426
00:26:18,772 --> 00:26:21,189
- Agreed, now get outta here.

427
00:26:22,849 --> 00:26:23,766
- Let's go.

428
00:26:30,555 --> 00:26:31,725
- Show him the coat.

429
00:26:31,725 --> 00:26:34,526
- Look, we really messed it up,

430
00:26:34,526 --> 00:26:36,315
made it look like he was
in a fight or something.

431
00:26:36,315 --> 00:26:38,226
- We're gonna show the coat to Dad,

432
00:26:38,226 --> 00:26:41,611
tell them that we found it, in an alley.

433
00:26:41,611 --> 00:26:44,361
Let him draw his own conclusions.

434
00:26:45,202 --> 00:26:47,530
- You idiots, what are we doing with this?

435
00:26:47,530 --> 00:26:50,770
How come the police don't got it?

436
00:26:50,770 --> 00:26:51,603
- What?

437
00:26:53,029 --> 00:26:55,136
They look for it, but they're
not gonna find anything.

438
00:26:55,136 --> 00:26:58,027
There's no blood, nothing.

439
00:26:58,027 --> 00:27:00,549
So they return it to the grieving family.

440
00:27:00,549 --> 00:27:02,787
- The grieving family?

441
00:27:02,787 --> 00:27:03,620
- Yeah.

442
00:27:05,463 --> 00:27:08,296
- You don't feel anything, do you?

443
00:27:09,927 --> 00:27:10,760
- Feel?

444
00:27:12,067 --> 00:27:15,734
I feel we did what was
right for the family.

445
00:27:17,927 --> 00:27:20,927
- Welcome to the presidential suite.

446
00:27:24,564 --> 00:27:26,647
- Bye, Father, I'm sorry.

447
00:27:32,039 --> 00:27:32,872
- Well?

448
00:27:33,769 --> 00:27:35,547
- What he say?

449
00:27:35,547 --> 00:27:36,784
- The boys can't handle this.

450
00:27:36,784 --> 00:27:38,809
I mean, they're not even making any sense.

451
00:27:38,809 --> 00:27:40,888
They're all over the place.

452
00:27:40,888 --> 00:27:42,937
- He said that he loves us,

453
00:27:42,937 --> 00:27:45,851
and that he trusts that
we're doing everything

454
00:27:45,851 --> 00:27:47,851
that we can to find Joe.

455
00:27:50,420 --> 00:27:51,736
- That's perfect.

456
00:27:51,736 --> 00:27:54,627
- Jacob, please, sit down.

457
00:27:54,627 --> 00:27:57,675
- I gotta go there, talk to the police.

458
00:27:57,675 --> 00:28:01,769
- If we leave tonight, we
could be in New York tomorrow.

459
00:28:01,769 --> 00:28:04,021
- I can look for Joseph myself.

460
00:28:04,021 --> 00:28:06,202
- Joseph is my son too.

461
00:28:06,202 --> 00:28:08,285
(crying)

462
00:28:12,153 --> 00:28:12,986
- Mother?

463
00:28:12,986 --> 00:28:15,439
- Rachel, are you all right?

464
00:28:15,439 --> 00:28:17,106
- It's not the baby.

465
00:28:18,318 --> 00:28:19,927
- I'm sorry, I'll be all right.

466
00:28:19,927 --> 00:28:21,163
- Shall I call the doctor?

467
00:28:21,163 --> 00:28:22,163
- No, don't.

468
00:28:23,008 --> 00:28:24,245
- [Diane] Are you sure you're all right?

469
00:28:24,245 --> 00:28:25,995
- Yes, darling, fine.

470
00:28:27,036 --> 00:28:28,036
- I'll stay.

471
00:28:28,994 --> 00:28:30,827
- No, don't stay.

472
00:28:30,827 --> 00:28:32,660
Jacob, listen, you go.

473
00:28:34,514 --> 00:28:35,514
I'm worried.

474
00:28:36,360 --> 00:28:38,090
I'm frightened, I don't know why.

475
00:28:38,090 --> 00:28:41,353
Not just about Joseph, about all the boys.

476
00:28:41,353 --> 00:28:43,186
- Room service please.

477
00:28:44,244 --> 00:28:46,827
(upbeat music)

478
00:29:17,550 --> 00:29:19,450
(yelling)

479
00:29:19,450 --> 00:29:20,283
Noooo!

480
00:29:24,605 --> 00:29:26,188
- [Thompsonn] Easy.

481
00:29:27,182 --> 00:29:29,849
- [Joseph] Let me go, let me go.

482
00:29:31,169 --> 00:29:32,628
- Easy.

483
00:29:32,628 --> 00:29:33,461
- Your friends went to much trouble

484
00:29:33,461 --> 00:29:37,016
and expense to put you here,
and here you will stay.

485
00:29:37,016 --> 00:29:38,711
Now you have a choice.

486
00:29:38,711 --> 00:29:42,258
Stay put, do what you're told
and keep your mouth shut,

487
00:29:42,258 --> 00:29:43,756
and you'll survive.

488
00:29:43,756 --> 00:29:46,506
Otherwise, in here you're nobody.

489
00:29:48,185 --> 00:29:50,976
Out there, you're as good as dead.

490
00:29:50,976 --> 00:29:52,811
I can and will do whatever is necessary

491
00:29:52,811 --> 00:29:56,161
to maintain the status quo, understood?

492
00:29:56,161 --> 00:29:58,164
- You can't just make me disappear.

493
00:29:58,164 --> 00:30:01,020
- I already did, happens all the time.

494
00:30:01,020 --> 00:30:04,305
- These friends of mine, they
didn't tell you, did they?

495
00:30:04,305 --> 00:30:06,198
- Tell me what?

496
00:30:06,198 --> 00:30:08,706
- They're my brothers.

497
00:30:08,706 --> 00:30:12,363
Puts you in a rather uncomfortable
position, doesn't it?

498
00:30:12,363 --> 00:30:13,196
- No.

499
00:30:14,185 --> 00:30:15,768
Get him outta here.

500
00:30:21,582 --> 00:30:24,520
- You said that no deceased person fitting

501
00:30:24,520 --> 00:30:27,556
his description has come in
in the last couple of days,

502
00:30:27,556 --> 00:30:30,389
and that you've checked hospitals.

503
00:30:31,428 --> 00:30:34,804
Because you see, he sometimes has,

504
00:30:34,804 --> 00:30:37,198
I don't know, I mean,
something like a lapse.

505
00:30:37,198 --> 00:30:39,181
- Maybe we should just go
out and start looking again.

506
00:30:39,181 --> 00:30:40,922
We did come up with his coat.

507
00:30:40,922 --> 00:30:44,169
- Maybe he was epileptic, you
know, maybe it was epilepsy.

508
00:30:44,169 --> 00:30:45,903
You asked me that 10 times,
I already told you that.

509
00:30:45,903 --> 00:30:47,049
Last time I saw him was in the morning.

510
00:30:47,049 --> 00:30:48,837
- I remember what he had for breakfast.

511
00:30:48,837 --> 00:30:51,101
We'd always get together as a family,

512
00:30:51,101 --> 00:30:51,934
have our breakfast together.

513
00:30:51,934 --> 00:30:54,384
- I just turned back, and
I looked, I didn't see him.

514
00:30:54,384 --> 00:30:55,901
I figured, well, he just
stepped into the shop.

515
00:30:55,901 --> 00:30:59,484
So I went back, maybe
I don't know, two or.

516
00:31:01,989 --> 00:31:04,572
- Please, God, where is my son?

517
00:31:06,263 --> 00:31:09,013
(dramatic music)

518
00:31:14,099 --> 00:31:15,754
- Everyone works.

519
00:31:15,754 --> 00:31:19,486
(speaking foreign language)

520
00:31:19,486 --> 00:31:21,118
No one looks up at me.

521
00:31:21,118 --> 00:31:22,987
You don't wanna see my dirty face.

522
00:31:22,987 --> 00:31:24,629
Nobody wants to look at my dirty face.

523
00:31:24,629 --> 00:31:26,574
Everyone look at the machines.

524
00:31:26,574 --> 00:31:28,491
No one wants to see me.

525
00:31:29,546 --> 00:31:30,963
And nobody talks.

526
00:31:34,887 --> 00:31:37,128
(speaking foreign language)

527
00:31:37,128 --> 00:31:40,854
Everyone works, everyone, everyone.

528
00:31:40,854 --> 00:31:42,033
- You okay?

529
00:31:42,033 --> 00:31:42,950
Let me see.

530
00:31:44,752 --> 00:31:46,625
Who did this to you?

531
00:31:46,625 --> 00:31:47,625
Huh, he did?

532
00:31:49,798 --> 00:31:52,509
- Mr. Childress wants to see you.

533
00:31:52,509 --> 00:31:54,842
- This woman needs a doctor.

534
00:31:55,738 --> 00:31:57,763
- She's lucky she can still walk.

535
00:31:57,763 --> 00:31:59,202
- No one deserves that.

