00:41:09,592 --> 00:41:10,425
- Maybe.

703
00:41:12,459 --> 00:41:14,574
You know, my wife liked these.

704
00:41:14,574 --> 00:41:15,657
- Oh, Martha.

705
00:41:16,947 --> 00:41:19,436
You know, she had dreams
of becoming a designer.

706
00:41:19,436 --> 00:41:20,853
She even studied.

707
00:41:22,382 --> 00:41:25,540
- If I establish this
legitimate front then disappear,

708
00:41:25,540 --> 00:41:27,206
how do I know I won't be arrested

709
00:41:27,206 --> 00:41:29,029
five minutes after I close down?

710
00:41:29,029 --> 00:41:31,165
- Well, because the way this is set up,

711
00:41:31,165 --> 00:41:33,406
the authorities will never find you.

712
00:41:33,406 --> 00:41:36,882
- Except through you,
another interesting problem.

713
00:41:36,882 --> 00:41:37,715
- No, no.

714
00:41:38,930 --> 00:41:40,763
I, I give you my word.

715
00:41:42,542 --> 00:41:45,095
If it doesn't work,
you can always go back.

716
00:41:45,095 --> 00:41:46,612
- Well the accountant thinks it'll work.

717
00:41:46,612 --> 00:41:48,940
I mean, if we're cautious.

718
00:41:48,940 --> 00:41:52,591
And my wife, well, she
hates this place as it is.

719
00:41:52,591 --> 00:41:53,996
I'll tell you what.

720
00:41:53,996 --> 00:41:57,137
Bring Martha and Emily to my office

721
00:41:57,137 --> 00:41:59,604
this Friday, and we'll talk.

722
00:41:59,604 --> 00:42:01,241
- Okay.

723
00:42:01,241 --> 00:42:04,182
