01:18:35,282 --> 01:18:36,115
- Sure.

1326
01:18:37,578 --> 01:18:38,661
What company?

1327
01:18:39,601 --> 01:18:43,434
- [Parker] Keller
Manufacturing, any relation?

1328
01:18:44,291 --> 01:18:45,124
- What?

1329
01:18:46,251 --> 01:18:48,714
- Keller Manufacturing.

1330
01:18:48,714 --> 01:18:51,187
What's wrong, you know these guys?

1331
01:18:51,187 --> 01:18:52,020
- No.

1332
01:18:53,382 --> 01:18:54,715
No, no, nothing.

1333
01:18:57,884 --> 01:19:01,358
Uh, give me, give me five minutes please.

1334
01:19:01,358 --> 01:19:02,191
- Sure.

1335
01:19:05,758 --> 01:19:06,964
- Parker?

1336
01:19:06,964 --> 01:19:08,660
- [Parker] Yeah?

1337
01:19:08,660 --> 01:19:09,493
- Did you,

1338
01:19:10,942 --> 01:19:12,677
did you give them my name?

1339
01:19:12,677 --> 01:19:15,242
- No, they were waiting to see Saunders.

1340
01:19:15,242 --> 01:19:16,575
- Don't, let me.

1341
01:19:17,705 --> 01:19:19,455
- Sure, five minutes.

1342
01:19:37,512 --> 01:19:38,512
- Thank you.

1343
01:19:41,354 --> 01:19:43,702
- Good evening, thanks
for seeing us so late.

1344
01:19:43,702 --> 01:19:44,606
I'm Robert Keller.

1345
01:19:44,606 --> 01:19:48,340
These are my brothers,
Simon, Justin, Ashton.

1346
01:19:48,340 --> 01:19:50,644
We're from Keller Manufacturing.

1347
01:19:50,644 --> 01:19:51,646
Clothing.

1348
01:19:51,646 --> 01:19:54,144
- So you told my assistant.

1349
01:19:54,144 --> 01:19:55,394
- That's right.

1350
01:19:56,281 --> 01:19:59,948
We understand that you're
in the position, this bank,

1351
01:19:59,948 --> 01:20:03,943
this institution, of giving
rather substantial loans.

1352
01:20:03,943 --> 01:20:04,776
- Go on.

1353
01:20:06,293 --> 01:20:07,641
- Mr., I--

1354
01:20:07,641 --> 01:20:08,599
- [Joseph] Gray.

1355
01:20:08,599 --> 01:20:10,266
- Mr. Gray, we are a

1356
01:20:12,053 --> 01:20:15,136
proud foundation, 40 years, clothing.

1357
01:20:18,160 --> 01:20:19,849
We have great references.

1358
01:20:19,849 --> 01:20:22,357
- If it's such a successful company,

1359
01:20:22,357 --> 01:20:23,940
why do you need me?

1360
01:20:24,900 --> 01:20:27,947
Or perhaps you're borrowing in panic.

1361
01:20:27,947 --> 01:20:30,953
Taking money from smaller
firms in real need.

1362
01:20:30,953 --> 01:20:31,786
- No.

1363
01:20:32,763 --> 01:20:37,026
And there's more than
just business at stake.

1364
01:20:37,026 --> 01:20:39,580
We have personal considerations.

1365
01:20:39,580 --> 01:20:40,985
People.

1366
01:20:40,985 --> 01:20:43,168
- What my brother means to
say is that this is a business

1367
01:20:43,168 --> 01:20:46,251
that our father started 40 years ago.

1368
01:20:47,647 --> 01:20:50,830
And he's depending on us, Mr. Gray.

1369
01:20:50,830 --> 01:20:54,160
- As are the workers and their families.

1370
01:20:54,160 --> 01:20:56,903
And our own families, as well.

1371
01:20:56,903 --> 01:20:58,648
- With so much at stake,
why isn't your father

1372
01:20:58,648 --> 01:21:00,767
here to see me himself?

1373
01:21:00,767 --> 01:21:03,071
- He couldn't make it out here.

1374
01:21:03,071 --> 01:21:04,404
It's his memory.

1375
01:21:05,465 --> 01:21:07,048
He's quite elderly.

1376
01:21:08,164 --> 01:21:12,331
- He hasn't traveled much
since the death of our mother.

1377
01:21:13,520 --> 01:21:14,437
Stepmother.

1378
01:21:16,254 --> 01:21:17,254
- I'm sorry.

1379
01:21:18,920 --> 01:21:20,837
May I ask how she died?

1380
01:21:21,968 --> 01:21:23,051
- Childbirth.

1381
01:21:24,488 --> 01:21:27,238
That's our youngest brother, Ben.

1382
01:21:29,619 --> 01:21:32,286
- The death of a wife, a mother,

1383
01:21:35,186 --> 01:21:36,269
is very hard.

1384
01:21:38,031 --> 01:21:41,031
It's fortunate that the child lived.

1385
01:21:42,881 --> 01:21:46,348
Still, the man who
stands to lose the most,

1386
01:21:46,348 --> 01:21:47,789
meaning your father, should be here

1387
01:21:47,789 --> 01:21:50,744
to negotiate with me himself.

1388
01:21:50,744 --> 01:21:52,494
- He can't, he won't.

1389
01:21:53,554 --> 01:21:55,054
He hates New York.

1390
01:21:57,460 --> 01:21:59,364
He lost a son here.

1391
01:21:59,364 --> 01:22:00,197
- Lost?

1392
01:22:04,830 --> 01:22:06,451
- He disappeared.

1393
01:22:06,451 --> 01:22:09,656
A few months before our mother died.

1394
01:22:09,656 --> 01:22:12,627
He may have been murdered.

1395
01:22:12,627 --> 01:22:15,496
- Yeah, and I was the one who was supposed

1396
01:22:15,496 --> 01:22:17,496
to look after him, yeah.

1397
01:22:20,974 --> 01:22:22,724
- We're all to blame.

1398
01:22:23,641 --> 01:22:24,474
All of us.

1399
01:22:27,588 --> 01:22:28,588
- It's late.

1400
01:22:29,873 --> 01:22:34,040
Give me your financial report,
and I will look it over.

1401
01:22:36,015 --> 01:22:37,700
- You may have some questions

1402
01:22:37,700 --> 01:22:39,848
regarding some of the
family history with loans.

1403
01:22:39,848 --> 01:22:42,098
- I will give you my answer

1404
01:22:42,954 --> 01:22:44,420
tomorrow.

1405
01:22:44,420 --> 01:22:46,726
- You've been most kind.

1406
01:22:46,726 --> 01:22:47,559
Thank you.

1407
01:22:53,272 --> 01:22:56,022
- Carl, please, please excuse me.

1408
01:23:08,876 --> 01:23:12,398
(dramatic music)

1409
01:23:12,398 --> 01:23:14,648
Why do you send them to me?

1410
01:23:16,435 --> 01:23:18,102
After all this time.

1411
01:23:19,450 --> 01:23:20,283
I can

1412
01:23:22,152 --> 01:23:22,985
ruin them.

1413
01:23:26,007 --> 01:23:29,174
Destroy everything they've worked for.

1414
01:23:31,903 --> 01:23:34,570
And they wouldn't even know why.

1415
01:23:37,292 --> 01:23:38,125
My mother.

1416
01:23:42,416 --> 01:23:43,249
Damn them.

1417
01:23:50,832 --> 01:23:51,665
19 years.

1418
01:23:55,545 --> 01:23:57,378
How do I forgive that?

1419
01:24:00,147 --> 01:24:02,397
How do I forgive any of it?

1420
01:24:04,659 --> 01:24:06,258
- This is a generous loan.

1421
01:24:06,258 --> 01:24:10,002
And the rates, they seem more than fair.

1422
01:24:10,002 --> 01:24:11,296
Justin.

1423
01:24:11,296 --> 01:24:14,297
- Everything seems to be in order,

1424
01:24:14,297 --> 01:24:18,326
but I'm unclear on these
last two provisions.

1425
01:24:18,326 --> 01:24:22,070
- The first provision simply
means that for the duration

1426
01:24:22,070 --> 01:24:25,368
of the loan, one of you will stay here

1427
01:24:25,368 --> 01:24:27,730
and be available for consultation.

1428
01:24:27,730 --> 01:24:29,498
- That's unheard of.

1429
01:24:29,498 --> 01:24:32,264
- The second requires Jacob Keller,

1430
01:24:32,264 --> 01:24:35,706
as principal owner of
Keller Manufacturing,

1431
01:24:35,706 --> 01:24:37,036
to come to New York and sign the papers

1432
01:24:37,036 --> 01:24:41,203
in person, and all of his
sons will accompany him.

1433
01:24:42,637 --> 01:24:44,720
Those are the conditions.

1434
01:24:47,014 --> 01:24:49,981
- Mr. Gray, with all due respect,

1435
01:24:49,981 --> 01:24:53,020
Robert and Justin have power of attorney.

1436
01:24:53,020 --> 01:24:55,966
Father's presence, it's uncalled for.

1437
01:24:55,966 --> 01:24:58,799
- These are special circumstances.

1438
01:25:00,387 --> 01:25:02,131
It is a requirement,

1439
01:25:02,131 --> 01:25:05,393
if you wish a loan to save
your father's business.

1440
01:25:05,393 --> 01:25:06,606
- I'll stay.

1441
01:25:06,606 --> 01:25:07,837
- What?

1442
01:25:07,837 --> 01:25:09,524
- I said I'll stay.

1443
01:25:09,524 --> 01:25:10,593
- Why?

1444
01:25:10,593 --> 01:25:12,603
- I have my reasons.

1445
01:25:12,603 --> 01:25:14,855
Let's just say I owe it to Dad.

1446
01:25:14,855 --> 01:25:15,859
I'll be all right.

1447
01:25:15,859 --> 01:25:16,777
- [Robert] Are you sure?

1448
01:25:16,777 --> 01:25:18,419
- Yeah.

1449
01:25:18,419 --> 01:25:19,502
- Good, fine.

1450
01:25:22,777 --> 01:25:24,444
- Is this guy wacko?

1451
01:25:25,327 --> 01:25:26,621
He's certifiable.

1452
01:25:26,621 --> 01:25:29,204
Nobody does business like this.

1453
01:25:30,151 --> 01:25:32,346
- It was the only way to get the money.

1454
01:25:32,346 --> 01:25:33,413
- Well return it.

1455
01:25:33,413 --> 01:25:35,051
We don't need it, not this way.

1456
01:25:35,051 --> 01:25:36,796
- Father, listen.

1457
01:25:36,796 --> 01:25:39,033
Please, we do need the money.

1458
01:25:39,033 --> 01:25:40,809
Without it, we stand to lose everything.

1459
01:25:40,809 --> 01:25:42,162
- We'll get it someplace else.

1460
01:25:42,162 --> 01:25:44,600
- Don't you think we tried?

1461
01:25:44,600 --> 01:25:46,682
Everyone's hurting now, Dad.

1462
01:25:46,682 --> 01:25:48,100
- But why keep Simon?

1463
01:25:48,100 --> 01:25:49,630
And why would this man want Dad?

1464
01:25:49,630 --> 01:25:50,508
- I don't know.

1465
01:25:50,508 --> 01:25:51,949
- Benjamin's staying here.

1466
01:25:51,949 --> 01:25:53,949
I'll not risk his going.

1467
01:25:55,145 --> 01:25:58,986
- Well, Mr. Gray, he said
all of us together, Dad.

1468
01:25:58,986 --> 01:25:59,819
I'm sorry.

1469
01:26:01,308 --> 01:26:03,166
- I fear for Benjamin
because he's my youngest,

1470
01:26:03,166 --> 01:26:05,684
but I fear for all of you.

1471
01:26:05,684 --> 01:26:08,434
So I'll go and see this Mr. Gray.

1472
01:26:09,622 --> 01:26:11,372
- I'm going with you.

1473
01:26:14,188 --> 01:26:17,313
Don't look at me like that, I'm going.

1474
01:26:17,313 --> 01:26:20,063
(dramatic music)

1475
01:26:24,145 --> 01:26:25,672
- How long are we supposed to wait?

1476
01:26:25,672 --> 01:26:26,924
We've been here half an hour already.

1477
01:26:26,924 --> 01:26:28,757
- As long as it takes.

1478
01:26:29,817 --> 01:26:31,220
Simon.

1479
01:26:31,220 --> 01:26:32,829
Are you all right?

1480
01:26:32,829 --> 01:26:34,755
- Yeah, I'm fine, really.

1481
01:26:34,755 --> 01:26:36,137
It's good to see all of you.

1482
01:26:36,137 --> 01:26:37,328
- Do you know what's going on here?

1483
01:26:37,328 --> 01:26:38,161
- Yeah.

1484
01:26:38,161 --> 01:26:39,186
- So where is this Mr. Gray.

1485
01:26:39,186 --> 01:26:40,446
- Well that's just it.

1486
01:26:40,446 --> 01:26:41,435
I couldn't tell you right now.

1487
01:26:41,435 --> 01:26:43,584
I haven't seen that much of him.

1488
01:26:43,584 --> 01:26:45,699
His assistant, Mr. Parker,

1489
01:26:45,699 --> 01:26:48,880
wanted me to give this to you, Dad.

1490
01:26:48,880 --> 01:26:50,547
- Like the big city?

1491
01:26:52,990 --> 01:26:55,740
- Diane, I don't have my glasses.

1492
01:26:57,263 --> 01:26:59,555
- Dear Mr. Keller,

1493
01:26:59,555 --> 01:27:03,079
I will meet you and your
sons in my home at seven p.m.

1494
01:27:03,079 --> 01:27:06,150
Transportation is awaiting.

1495
01:27:06,150 --> 01:27:06,983
Mr. Gray.

1496
01:27:10,051 --> 01:27:12,134
- Can't we sit down?

1497
01:27:12,134 --> 01:27:15,215
- Father, I'm sure it would
be all right if you sat.

1498
01:27:15,215 --> 01:27:16,318
- [Jacob] It's all right, all right.

1499
01:27:16,318 --> 01:27:17,319
I'll only have to stand a while.

1500
01:27:17,319 --> 01:27:20,088
- [Justin] Maybe we're
supposed to start without him.

1501
01:27:20,088 --> 01:27:21,088
- Gentlemen.

1502
01:27:24,494 --> 01:27:26,244
Thank you for coming.

1503
01:27:41,250 --> 01:27:42,083
Welcome.

1504
01:27:43,264 --> 01:27:44,097
All of you.

1505
01:27:44,097 --> 01:27:46,506
- What's this all about?

1506
01:27:46,506 --> 01:27:47,710
Why are we here?

1507
01:27:47,710 --> 01:27:51,793
- I would like to propose
a toast to your family.

1508
01:27:53,626 --> 01:27:56,293
To those who are no longer here.

1509
01:27:57,753 --> 01:28:00,920
To those who sit in health before you,

1510
01:28:03,140 --> 01:28:05,307
and to those who are lost.

1511
01:28:08,194 --> 01:28:09,611
But now is found.

1512
01:28:10,725 --> 01:28:11,558
Salute.

1513
01:28:22,001 --> 01:28:22,834
Father.

1514
01:28:25,182 --> 01:28:26,182
I am Joseph.

1515
01:28:30,548 --> 01:28:31,381
Your son.

1516
01:28:39,009 --> 01:28:40,092
- That can't.

1517
01:28:42,394 --> 01:28:44,227
This is too cruel, no.

1518
01:28:46,401 --> 01:28:47,740
No, no, no.

1519
01:28:47,740 --> 01:28:49,323
- Yes, I am Joseph.

1520
01:28:50,608 --> 01:28:52,700
My mother is Rachel.

1521
01:28:52,700 --> 01:28:55,861
We had a house next to an empty lot.

1522
01:28:55,861 --> 01:28:58,255
My room was down the hall from Ash.

1523
01:28:58,255 --> 01:29:01,244
I worked one summer at the factory.

1524
01:29:01,244 --> 01:29:03,596
You gave me a coat.

1525
01:29:03,596 --> 01:29:05,679
(crying)

1526
01:29:18,965 --> 01:29:20,298
- What happened?

1527
01:29:21,227 --> 01:29:23,635
What happened, what happened?

1528
01:29:23,635 --> 01:29:25,244
- To be honest, Father,
those are not memories

1529
01:29:25,244 --> 01:29:26,661
I wish to recall.

1530
01:29:27,626 --> 01:29:28,459
Ever.

1531
01:29:31,620 --> 01:29:33,287
But I will say this.

1532
01:29:37,158 --> 01:29:39,491
What might have destroyed me

1533
01:29:40,565 --> 01:29:43,141
has instead shaped me.

1534
01:29:43,141 --> 01:29:45,511
Shaped this moment.

1535
01:29:45,511 --> 01:29:47,344
I am here to help you.

1536
01:29:49,475 --> 01:29:50,392
All of you.

1537
01:29:51,624 --> 01:29:54,124
And many other people besides.

1538
01:29:59,947 --> 01:30:03,408
(dramatic music)

1539
01:30:03,408 --> 01:30:05,158
- Joseph, forgive me.

1540
01:30:09,595 --> 01:30:12,116
- Forgiveness will always be in my heart.

1541
01:30:12,116 --> 01:30:14,116
I know what you planned.

1542
01:30:15,164 --> 01:30:17,914
But fate always takes its course.

1543
01:30:21,114 --> 01:30:22,864
We are all right now.

1544
01:30:25,096 --> 01:30:25,929
All of us.

1545
01:30:29,067 --> 01:30:32,484
In time, you will see what I say is true.

1546
01:30:33,386 --> 01:30:34,719
A second chance.

1547
01:30:36,753 --> 01:30:40,305
(glasses clinking)

1548
01:30:40,305 --> 01:30:44,676
- To that grace which
has brought us together.

1549
01:30:44,676 --> 01:30:46,093
- To my children.

1550
01:30:49,255 --> 01:30:50,505
I love you all.

1551
01:30:56,512 --> 01:30:57,512
- Thank you.

1552
01:31:00,425 --> 01:31:03,175
(dramatic music)

1553
